---
title: Le Wagon Middleman boilerplate
---

<div class="page-container top-circle">
  <div class="title-center">
    <!-- profile image -->
    <%= image_tag "images/noemipic.jpg", alt:"author image", class:"avatar-lg" %>
    <h1>Noemi Ashizuka</h1>
    <h2>Web Developer in Tokyo</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="bio-long">
    <p>
    My name is Noemi and I'm from Italy. I have lived in Tokyo for almost 3 years 
    now and before Tokyo I was in London for 8 years. I completed Le Wagon 
    coding bootcamp in March 2020 and I'm currently looking for opportunities. I am working
    on a few personal projects at the moment, you can check my github. I feel like being a developer
    is great because there's always something new to learn and I love learning new things.
    </p>
    <!-- dropdown -->
    <div class="skills-container">
      <%= partial 'dropdown' %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h1 class="title-stripe">Projects</h1>
  <div class="half-page">
    <!-- project 1 -->
    <div class="project-content">
      <div class="project-img">
        <!-- image carousel -->
        <%= partial('carousel', locals: { carouselControls: 'carousel_cc', image1: 'cc_home.png', image2: 'cc_profile.png', image3: 'cc_look.png', image4: 'cc_look_show.png', class_set: 'd-block w-100 slide-tall'}) %>
      </div>
      <div class="project-info">
        <h1>Clever Closet</h1>
        <h3 class="text-clear">Ruby on Rails, HTML, SCSS, JavaScript, AJAX</h3>
        <p>Clever Closet is an app to manage your wardrobe and help reduce the impact of fast fashion on the environment. How does it do that? Simple, with Clever
        Clothes you can share clothes with friends, create looks for yourself and your friends to make the most of the clothes you already own. 
        </p>
        <p>Role: team manager.</p>
        <div class="icons-inline">
          <i class="fas fa-gem"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-html5"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-css3-alt"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-js-square"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-trello"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-figma"></i>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- project 2 -->
    <div class="project-content">
      <div class="project-info">
        <h1>Obi</h1>
        <h3 class="text-clear">Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, JavaScript</h3>
        <p>Obi is a marketplace where people can rent or lend kimonos of many different types.</p>
        <p>Role: team manager.</p>
        <div class="icons-inline">
          <i class="fas fa-gem"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-html5"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-css3-alt"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-js-square"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-trello"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-figma"></i>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="project-img-lg">
        <!-- image carousel -->
        <%= partial('carousel', locals: { carouselControls: 'carousel_obi', image1: 'obi_home.png', image2: 'obi_listings.png', image3: 'obi_show.png', image4: 'obi_dashyuka.png', class_set: 'd-block w-100 slide-short'}) %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- project 3 -->
      <div class="project-content"> 
        <div class="project-img-lg">
        <!-- image carousel -->
          <%= partial('carousel', locals: { carouselControls: 'carousel_bc', image1: 'bc_home.png', image2: 'bc_card_one.png', image3: 'bc_card_two.png', image4: 'bc_list.png', class_set: 'd-block w-100 slide-short'}) %>
        </div>
        <div class="project-info">
          <h1>Bartender Cocktail</h1>
          <h3 class="text-clear">Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, JavaScript</h3>
          <p>Project for Le Wagon bootcamp, developed in two days. The purpose was to learn how to develop an app
          with complex databases relations. Also cocktails are fun to make and look amazing. </p>
          <div class="icons-inline">
            <i class="fas fa-gem"></i>
            <i class="fab fa-html5"></i>
            <i class="fab fa-css3-alt"></i>
            <i class="fab fa-js-square"></i>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- project 4 -->
    <div class="project-content">
      <div class="project-info">
        <h1>Sailor Warrior Maker</h1>
        <h3 class="text-clear">Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, JavaScript</h3>
        <p>Le Wagon weekend challenge. Developed in two days. I decided to go for something I am passionate about and created an app
        where people can upload their own Sailor Scout and choose powers for them.</p>
        <div class="icons-inline">
          <i class="fas fa-gem"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-html5"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-css3-alt"></i>
          <i class="fab fa-js-square"></i>
        </div>
      </div>
        <div class="project-img-lg">
        <!-- image carousel -->
        <%= partial('carousel', locals: { carouselControls: 'carousel_swm', image1: 'swm_home.png', image2: 'swm_list.png', image3: 'swm_card.png', image4: 'swm_card_two.png', class_set: 'd-block w-100 slide-short'}) %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div> <!--half-page(column) -->
</div><!-- .welcome -->
